{
  "texts": [
    "Those analyses exploit the GPD overlap representation, with light-front wave functions constrained by π and K valence-quark DFs.",
    "Profiting from such studies, Ref.",
    "[37] delivered a data driven prediction for the pion mass distribution, showing that the pion's mass radius is ≈ 20% smaller than its charge radius.Herein, we adopt a less phenomenological approach.",
    "Namely, using continuum Schwinger function methods (CSMs) [38,39], we solve the probe+meson scattering problem at leading-order of the truncation scheme introduced in Refs.",
    "Therewith, we also unify π and K electromagnetic and gravitational distributions with predictions for an array of hadron structural properties that range over systems with up-to three heavy quarks, e.g., Refs."
  ]
}